      "date": "2013-01-05 03:29:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nDo we still need the processing for lr_server_data::lsd_ost_index during ofd_obd_connect() ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7f6206d166542f60e6e1da1286f3b03c4b2517d0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-05 03:58:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think we do, for validation purpose I think",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3a5cb459b6dd9d6b69f67fa027482b846c6f3011",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-05 05:00:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI think that are some redundant logic in following code section after your patch applied:\n\nstatic int ofd_parse_connect_data(const struct lu_env *env,\n                                  struct obd_export *exp,\n                                  struct obd_connect_data *data)\n{\n...\n        if (data->ocd_connect_flags & OBD_CONNECT_INDEX) {\n                struct lr_server_data *lsd = &ofd->ofd_lut.lut_lsd;\n                int                    index = lsd->lsd_ost_index;\n\n                if (!(lsd->lsd_feature_compat & OBD_COMPAT_OST)) {\n                        /* this will only happen on the first connect */\n                        lsd->lsd_ost_index = data->ocd_index;\n                        lsd->lsd_feature_compat |= OBD_COMPAT_OST;\n                        /* sync is not needed here as lut_client_add will\n                         * set exp_need_sync flag */\n                        tgt_server_data_update(env, &ofd->ofd_lut, 0);\n                } else if (index != data->ocd_index) {\n                        LCONSOLE_ERROR_MSG(0x136, \"Connection from %s to index\"\n                                           \" %u doesn't match actual OST index\"\n                                           \" %u in last_rcvd file, bad \"\n                                           \"configuration?\\n\",\n                                           obd_export_nid2str(exp), index,\n                                           data->ocd_index);\n                        RETURN(-EBADF);\n                }\n        }\n...\n}",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
